author: julianfoad
msg: Improve consistency of error reporting in 'svn' and 'svnadmin', mainly by
channeling nearly all errors thrown within sub_main() up to a single handler
This is a source code improvement: no functional change.
This is a follow-up to r1368252 which initially separated the initilization
and tear-down into a separate function from the bulk of the logic in these
two programs. It was my intention then to follow up with something like
this. Similar factorization of the other command-line tools will follow.
(sub_main): Let this return a standard Subversion error object, and add an
exit_code output parameter for those cases where a non-zero exit code is
